Package: SurveyNCD
Title: Tools for Self-Reported Health Indicators in Complex Surveys
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Sujon", "Mia", email = "REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_EMAIL@example.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides tools for analysing population health survey data
    (WHO STEPS, DHS, MICS, and similar complex sample surveys), where
    chronic conditions are self-reported rather than ICD-coded and
    estimates must account for stratification, clustering, and sampling
    weights. Includes a self-reported multimorbidity index based on the
    Functional Comorbidity Index (Groll et al. 2005), design-weighted
    population prevalence estimation via the 'survey' package, a
    survey-weighted concentration index for health inequality analysis,
    a DHS anthropometric z-score categoriser, a choropleth mapping
    helper, and exploratory survey-weighted gradient boosting (via
    'xgboost') with SHAP-based explainability. The gradient boosting
    component applies case weights but does not yet propagate cluster
    and strata design effects into variance estimates; it should be
    treated as exploratory rather than as design-based inference.
